latestPosts.caption:
1. Learned how to meet stupid deadlines.
Like stitch a fit in 3 hours type of deadlines. Sounds wild, but now when I’m working on last-minute film or styling projects, I don’t panic.

2. Got exposed to everything.
It wasn’t just fashion sketching. We did styling, photography, CAD, even jewellery modules. So now I can do ten things at once without losing my mind.

3. It builds your tolerance for chaos.
Fashion school is not glamorous. It’s glue guns, fabric markets, and crying at 3 AM. But that pressure-cooker vibe kinda prepares you for real-life work stress.

4. The name still adds credibility.
People know NIFT. Even if they don’t get what you studied, they respect the grind. It helps with freelance gigs and brand collabs too.

5. Doesn’t matter which centre you go to.
Honestly, syllabus is the same. Bhubaneswar, Chennai, Bombay ! what you do with your time there is what counts.

6.I made my best friends at NIFT.
Found my core gang & am always grateful to have met likeminded people in diff fonts lol 💖 
.
#Niftadmissions #Nift #fashionbusiness

latestPosts.caption:
This isn’t just tailoring.
This is temptation, stitched.

The Droplet Blazer.
For the ones who don’t beg for attention.
They just walk in wearing it.

Custom commissioned by @aryankatoch17

I didn’t design this jacket because I wanted to make outerwear.
I designed it because I needed something to hold me together when my mind felt like it was falling apart.

The cords on this piece aren’t just aesthetic.
They represent clutter ,creative chaos, overthinking, that constant feeling of too many tabs open.
That’s how Balav started.
Not from perfection. From chaos.

And in that mess, I kept going back to this one idea:
Everyone needs a black jacket.
But not just any black jacket.
One that’s oversized but still powerful. Gender Fluid. Is Versatile.
Comfortable but never boring.
A piece that adapts to your mood , with loops you can detach, shift, or leave hanging loose, just like your thoughts.

This is the kind of jacket you wear on your best days and your breakdown days.
It doesn’t judge. It just fits.

This jacket wasn’t made for everyone.
It was made for the ones who feel everything, all at once , and still show up.
Only a few pieces of our bestseller left

latestPosts.caption:
Tell you what? It sold!  I had no expectations, but here’s what intent got me. My idea was to create something beautiful, something that lights up a space and makes it look unique.
I added 3 filament bulbs & shipped this to my customer in Goa. Sometimes, new routes teach you things you never expected to learn or build on to.
Stop pleasing people, do what your heart says. People will always come around 🤍
🤭
